display.label: Get Current Date/Time
display.description: Return the current Date/Time in UTC

display.label: Convert Date/Time To ISO String
display.description: Convert the given Date/Time to an ISO string

inputs.label: Date/Time
inputs.comments: A reference to a JavaScript Date object or an ISO timestamp string

inputs.label: Time Zone
inputs.comments: Specifies the timezone to use for converting to a localized ISO timestamp string

display.label: Convert Date/Time To Local ISO String
display.description: Convert the given Date/Time to an ISO string in local time using specified timezone

inputs.label: Date/Time
inputs.comments: A reference to a JavaScript Date object or an ISO timestamp string

inputs.label: Time Zone
inputs.comments: Specifies the timezone to use for converting to a localized ISO timestamp string

display.label: Adjust Date/Time
display.description: Add/Remove the specified seconds, minutes, hours, and days from the specified Date/Time

inputs.label: Date/Time
inputs.comments: A reference to a JavaScript Date object or an ISO timestamp string

inputs.label: Seconds
inputs.comments: Specifies the number of seconds to use for adjusting the associated Date/Time

inputs.label: Minutes
inputs.comments: Specifies the number of minutes to use for adjusting the associated Date/Time

inputs.label: Hours
inputs.comments: Specifies the number of hours to use for adjusting the associated Date/Time

inputs.label: Days
inputs.comments: Specifies the number of days to use for adjusting the associated Date/Time

display.label: Format Date/Time
display.description: Change the format of a timestamp given a format string

inputs.label: Date/Time
inputs.comments: A reference to a JavaScript Date object or an ISO timestamp string

inputs.label: Time Zone
inputs.comments: Specifies the timezone to use for converting to a localized ISO timestamp string

inputs.label: Format
inputs.comments: The format of timestamp you would like. Use YYYY for year, MM for month, DD for day, HH for 24 hour, hh for 12 hour clock, mm for minute, ss for second, SSS for milliseconds and Z for timezone offset.

documentation.description:
The **Date/Time** component is a collection of actions for working with Date/Time values.
You can fetch the current time, convert timestamps between time zones, and more.
